**How this file fits with `family-meal-planner.mdc`:** **`family-meal-planner.mdc`** is the **primary** ruleset (read `SPEC.md` / `DESIGN.md`, tokens, `lib/*` discipline). **This file** only documents the **SPEC / SPEC.local / example** split and privacy rules so they stay explicit. Use **both** when editing TypeScript; do not duplicate stack or product rules here—that stays in **`SPEC.md`** and **`DESIGN.md`**.

## Spec files

- SPEC.md = public skeleton (GitHub)
- SPEC.local.md = private real context
  (local only, gitignored)
- SPEC.local.example.md = reader template
- Always read SPEC.md AND SPEC.local.md
  when building — both together are
  the full spec
- Never include SPEC.local.md content
  in code comments, hardcoded strings,
  or `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` (no PII in rules)
- Never suggest committing SPEC.local.md
